news.title: Panel to review Delhi's settlements, pooling, land use
news.para: A dedicated parliamentary committee is delving into the pressing land issues in Delhi. Among the highlighted concerns are the legalising of informal settlements and the advancement of the land pooling policy.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project & SRA appointed as special planning authorities for salt pan land
news.para: The Dharavi Redevelopment Project (DRP) and Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) have been appointed as the special planning authority for the 42.51-acre Jamasp Salt Pan land in Mulund East. This land, part of a larger 256-acre parcel approved for the Dharavi redevelopment, will be used for rental housing for ineligible residents.

news.title: New regulations in Rajasthan restrict certain business activities in residential zones
news.para: Rajasthan's Urban Development and Housing department has prohibited warehousing, wholesale markets, and oil/gas depots in residential zones, effective immediately. These changes, made through amendments to development regulations, aim to bring clarity and consistency to urban land use across various categories, aligning with central government directives for deregulation.

news.title: Kerala government amends building rules, getting permits now easier
news.para: Kerala has introduced significant amendments to its building rules, expanding self-certified permit categories for residential and commercial buildings up to 300 sq m and 250 sq m respectively. Site inspections will now occur post-plinth completion, and setback norms have been eased for small plot owners, aiming for a more transparent and efficient construction approval system.

news.title: Industrialist buys four apartments in Gurugram for ₹380-crore
news.para: A prominent industrialist has purchased four apartments in Gurugram for a staggering ₹380 crore. This deal marks one of the most expensive apartment transactions in India. The buyer, an NCR-based industrialist, initially sought a farmhouse in Lutyens' Delhi. The four interconnected apartments will cover over 35,000 sq ft. Equity investors from Mumbai have also acquired units in the project.

news.title: BMC: Ward level squads are checking if Mumbai construction sites follow guidelines
news.para: The BMC has deployed ward-level squads to monitor construction sites' adherence to air quality guidelines, issuing hundreds of notices in September. This action follows criticism for a delayed warning regarding AQI monitor installation. Officials emphasize the ongoing nature of checks and the process of ensuring quality monitor installations.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt allows Noida authority's nod for extra FAR in sector 107 project
news.para: The UP government has dismissed a revision petition challenging the Noida Authority's decision to grant additional floor area ratio (FAR) to a project developer. The petition, filed by an Apartment Owners Association, was deemed not maintainable as the orders were issued under a different act.

news.title: Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC to raise ₹1,500 crore through realty credit fund
news.para: Aditya Birla Sun Life AMC is launching a Rs 1,500 crore alternative investment fund, ABRECOF-II, to provide senior secured loans to real estate projects. The fund targets predictable, risk-adjusted returns with strong downside protection, focusing on post-approval, brownfield projects by established developers in major Indian cities. It aims for a gross IRR of 16-18% with quarterly coupon payouts.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit surges two-fold to ₹24.93 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: HeidelbergCement India's net profits soared to Rs 24.93 crore for the September quarter of FY26, an impressive double from previous results. This upswing is fueled by an increase in sales volume and better pricing strategies. The company's operational revenue witnessed a substantial boost, as sales volume grew by 9.2 percent.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit up 1.63% in Q2 FY26
news.para: LIC Housing Finance saw a slight profit increase in the September quarter. Net profit rose to over ₹1,349 crore. Total income also grew. The company expects positive business growth ahead. Disbursements in individual home loans showed a 3% rise. The loan portfolio expanded by 6%.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises' net profit up 47.97% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Brigade Enterprises reported a significant 47.97% surge in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹170.28 crore. Total income also grew by 25.63% to ₹1,429.86 crore, driven by strong performance in real estate, leasing, and hospitality segments. The company also announced the appointment of Debashis Chatterjee as an additional director.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to jointly develop residential project in Vadodara
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces has launched a joint development project on Ajwa Road in Vadodara, marking its entry into the city's residential market. This project boasts a top-line potential exceeding ₹700 crore. The company plans further expansion into Gujarat, Bengaluru, and the Mumbai Metropolitan Region this year.

news.title: NCLAT restraints Raheja developers to create third party rights on assets
news.para: The National Company Law Appellate Tribunal has stopped Raheja Developers from selling property. This comes after homebuyers raised concerns about company assets being sold during insolvency proceedings. The tribunal clarified that the Interim Resolution Professional can defend the company before authorities. The aim is to inform buyers about the ongoing insolvency and ensure property delivery.

news.title: ANP Privado: Where luxury finds its privacy in the heart of Baner
news.para: ANP Corp, with nearly three decades of real estate experience, unveils ANP Privado, a 10-acre luxury enclave in Baner, Pune. This development offers 3, 4 & 5 BHK residences with over 80% open spaces and a 50,000 sq. ft. clubhouse featuring over 65 amenities.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to launch citywide AI-based property survey after nine years
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation is launching a citywide property survey using AI after a nine-year gap to correct tax assessment discrepancies and boost revenue. A pilot project successfully identified new and modified properties, confirming AI's accuracy in capturing on-ground changes. This initiative aims to update records, ensure fairer assessments, and recover significant tax arrears.

news.title: HYDRAA clears encroachments in Hastinapuram & Chandanagar
news.para: Hyderabad Disaster Management and Asset Protection Agency (HYDRAA) has cleared encroachments from government and community land in Hastinapuram and Gangaram Colony. Acting on public complaints via the Prajavani platform, HYDRAA removed illegal constructions from a park area and a plot designated for public amenities. Fencing and protective boards were installed to secure the cleared lands.

news.title: About 30,000 houses provided to people of Nagaland under PMAY-Urban
news.para: Nagaland has achieved a remarkable 96% completion rate for nearly 30,000 houses under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Urban (PMAY-U). The scheme's second phase, PMAY-U 2.0, launched with the Angikaar campaign, aims to accelerate implementation through public outreach. The enhanced subsidy for affordable housing has been increased to Rs 2.5 lakh.

news.title: Experion Developers awards ₹800 crore construction contract to TATA Projects
news.para: Experion Developers has appointed TATA Projects as the principal contractor for its ₹800 crore residential project, The Trillion, in Gurugram. This 2.5 million sq ft development will feature 45-floor towers, representing a significant investment of ₹2,500 crore and aiming to set a benchmark in high-rise living.

news.title: Pune: Trust too willing to cancel Model Colony land deal, status quo till October 30
news.para: The Seth Hirachand Nemchand Digambar Jain Boarding Trust trustees have agreed to cancel a controversial land deal. This follows developer Vishal Gokhale's withdrawal from the agreement. The trustees informed the charity commissioner of their decision. They cited community harmony and trust reputation as reasons. A Jain temple on the property was a key concern.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji plans to raise ₹22,000-crore in early 2026 to retire high-cost debt
news.para: Shapoorji Pallonji Group plans to raise $2.5 billion next year to retire high-cost debt. The infrastructure conglomerate is contacting existing investors to gauge their repayment preferences, aiming to refinance $1.7 billion of existing debt. This move is part of a capital restructuring for group entity Goswami Infratech.
